value.0: Excuse me, I must keep an eye on the maintenance hatch. We've got a lot of issues down there. You should go talk to Selan Flembok in reception if you need something.

Yes, yes. Selan told me to expect you along. I'll cut to the chase. The mine down below has become infested with Mynocks. Some dirty cargo ship docked with us a few days back, and I reckon the Mynocks came from there. 

I want you to make a dent in their population. Think you can get down there and dispose of a few for us?
Let's say five? Sounds a bit barbaric, but if you take out five of them, I'll give you a receipt for Selan. How's that sound?
How goes the hunt?
Well, hurry up! Every second you're here scratching your arse, they're multiplying!

Excellent! [He quickly writes out a receipt and hands it over to you.] Take this back to Selan. She'll know what to do with it.

If you need more work just stop by again.
Back for more, eh?
I'm sure you saw the malfunctioning droids while you were hunting those Mynocks, right?
You know where to find me.
Oh? Well, maybe the problem isn't quite as bad as it was. In any case I'd like for you to bust a few of them up for me. What do you say? Interested?
What do you say about heading down there and busting up a few of them?

They're MALFUNCTIONING droids, <boy/girl>! If we could just shut them off, we would. Some sort of malware got into their programming and now they're running haywire. The boys in engineering slack off, and now we have to pay the price.

If you can get close enough to them to shut them off, then be my guest. But more than likely you'll need to put them down the old fashioned way.

What do you say? Interested?

I knew I could count on you. Bust five of them up and get back to me when you've finished. You can keep whatever you find down there, too. I don't need a bunch of scrap metal. Just stop them from hurting someone.
How goes the hunt? Bust up some droids yet?

Nice job, <lad/lass>! I knew I could count on you. Here's a few credits for your trouble. Oh, and here's a datapad with some training information. You never know when it might come in handy. Come back later if you want more work to do. I've got a rather... troubling one to resolve.
I've got one more task for you. It's a pretty big one, too.
If you change your mind, I'll be here.

Alright. So, the boys down in engineering were performing experiments on a Colicoid which was shipped in recently. They were making great progress with splicing the Colicoid DNA to build more efficient capacitors. 

Then, as you know now, the droids started acting up. And between them and the Mynocks we had our hands full. It's quite amazing how many things went wrong at once, now that I think about it.

Anyway, that experimental Colicoid is on the loose down there. I need your help one more time to put it down for good. What do you say?
Great! I know I could count on you. I'd suggest making sure you're prepared. That thing is no cakewalk. I'll be waiting here for you. Don't you die on me, now.
How goes your hunt for the Colicoid?
Well, how about that! You're really something else, you know? Here's your reward.
Thanks for all your help, <lad/lass>.
Sorry, I'm not in the killing game. You'll have to find someone else.
I think I can manage that. How many do you want?
Like pulling teeth. Find someone else.
Sounds good! I'll be back soon.
Still working on it, I'll get back in touch with you soon.
I'll get back to it, then.
I managed to kill five of those Mynocks, like you asked.
Thanks.
Not right now.
Tell me about the other work you have.
On second thought, I'm busy right now.
No, I didn't see any down there.
I saw a few, yes.
Not right now.
Can't you just shut them off?
Sure, I can do that.
I'll be back soon.
I'm still working on it.
Those droids won't be hurting anyone anymore.
Thanks. See you later.
I can't take on any more work right now.
What have you got?
I need to think about it a little longer.
I'll take the job.
Thanks. I'll be back soon.
Still working on it. I need a little more time.
It's dead, now.
Thanks. [Accept Reward]
